{0 day11-opam-layer}

Opam-flavoured layer types that give domain meaning to the generic
{!day11-layer} storage. {!Day11_opam_layer.Build} is the recursive DAG node type: each
node carries a content-addressed hash, a package, direct dependency
nodes, and a universe identifier. {!Day11_opam_layer.Tool} aggregates multiple build
nodes into a single tool layer (e.g. odoc + deps). {!Day11_opam_layer.Build_meta}
reads and writes the [build.json] sidecar that marks a layer as an
opam package build and records installed libraries, docs, and patches.
{!Day11_opam_layer.Installed_files} scans a layer's overlay for [.cmi], [.cmti],
[.mld], and other documentation-relevant files. {!Day11_opam_layer.Opam_repo}
assembles an [opam-repository/] directory for container builds by
copying opam files from source repositories. {!Day11_opam_layer.Opamh} writes
synthetic opam switch-state files so the container sees stacked deps
as installed.

Depends on {!day11-layer}, {!day11-sys}, and {!page-solution}. This
library defines the types that {!day11-opam-build} and {!day11-doc}
operate on.

